message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order.
Today's Word is "Te" TE（hand)　#nihongo　
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「て」

In Japanese, like other languages, there are many words, idioms, or proverbs using parts of the body. "Te"(hand, て,手） is one of the most used body parts among all. How many Japanese phrases do you know using "Te"?

The phrase which describes me well today is “Neko no TE mo Karitai”（猫の手も借りたい, literally meaning "Extremely busy so I would even welcome the hand(help) of a cat", "I need every help I can get".)

日本語にも、他の言語と同じく体の一部を使った単語、熟語、ことわざがたくさんあります。その中でも「手」を使った言葉は数え切れません。
あなたはいくつ「手」を使った日本語、知っていますか？
今日の私の気分は「猫の【手】も借りたい」です。（K)
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1739&p=1&q=手&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
Do you know the origin of YUKATA (summer kimono)??
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=2102,979&p=1&q=
It is said that the word YUKATA comes from YU-KATABIRA（湯帷子、ゆかたびら）, which was worn by the nobles in the Heian period in the occasion of bathing. Since the steam bath was common at that time, they used to put on the YU-KATABIRA to absorb sweat or prevent from scalds.

As time passed, in the latter of the Edo period, YUKATA had widely spread to common people and gradually changed its usage from the former "bathing-suit" into townwear. It became more and more affordable and fashionable at the same time, which enabled people to enjoy YUKATA more easily.

Nowadays, YUKATA is considered as an icon for Japanese summer, stylish traditional garment which can enjoy casually. It is also popular among Japansese young men these days as a cool summer item.
Why don't you become a YUKATA beauty/handsome this summer:) !?

message.text:
Have you heard, saw, or even used Japanese unique & sophisticated products and designs?

In Japan, there are various kinds of products, small and big, which attract us in daily life.
Visitors often fall in love with the state of the art toilet, so-called "washlet".
Some enjoy the latest Shinkansen, a high-speed train moving 300km/h at the top speed, which is not just a vehicle anymore and continues to evolve.
Others like tiny inventions, such as "Cupmen", a product holding down the cover of an instant noodle cup. 

You can check these unique products and designs at "Japanese Design Today 100", JF's Traveling Exhibitions! Find your favorite Japanese products & designs, and let us know!
http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/exhibit/oversea/traveling/n_design_100.html

日本のデザイン、あなたはどう思いますか？例えばトイレ、新幹線、カップラーメンホルダー…。
私たちがいつも使っているデザインやモノからも日本文化が垣間見えます。

Japan: 8/29開催の新「現代日本のデザイン100選」展にまつわるトークイベントで、ぜひ体感してください！
http://www.jpf.go.jp/j/culture/exhibit/oversea/traveling/1408/08-01.html

Photos:
Cupmen1 Hold on
h concept co., ltd.
